UserPKG
=======
![alt logo](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dracolinux/UserPKG/master/res/hicolor/128x128/UserPKG.png)

Unprivileged package manager for Linux.

UserPKG is a convenient front-end for pkgsrc, simplifiying the installation and usage of third-party software. No administrator access needed.

Requirements
============

* Linux (primary testing happens on CentOS/RHEL 6)
 * Bash
 * GNU tar required (during first-run)
 * XZ required (during first-run)
 * NCurses libraries/headers required (yum install ncurses-devel)
* Build essentials

Status
======

Early beta, but usable. Most basic functions for v1 has been added, but may not have been tested over time, some functions may also not work as expected yet.

Roadmap/TODO
============

* Version 1.0.0
 * add cron job (check state, sync pkgsrc, check for updates, notify)
 * fix progressbar feedback
 * add pkgsrc sync blocker, also not run if bmake runs
 * Switch pkgsrc branch, simple conf settings
 * pause/stop/restart queue (stop works)
 * save/restore ui
 * move slow functions (search,list pkgs) to backend thread (added backend)
 * major code cleanup (code has just been added during the alpha run, do a review)
* Version 1.0.x
 * Bug fixes
* Version 1.1.0
 * dbus client (system/global support)
 * NetBSD/FreeBSD support
* Version 1.1.x
 * Bug fixes
* Version 2.0.0
 * move to libarchive (remove depend on tar+xz)
 * add windows/mingw support
 * add macos support
* Version 2.0.x
 * Bug fixes
* Version 3.0.0
 * binary pkg support (depends on SysPKG(on ice))

Install
=======

Download latest release or build your own. 1.0.0-beta1+ breaks with earlier alpha versions, please remove existing pkgsrc installation before running UserPKG.

```
rm -rf ~/.pkgdb* ~/pkg ~/pkgsrc ~/tmp/pkgsrc.tar.xz*
```

Build
=====

Requires Qt (4.6+) development files installed prior to build.

```
git submodule update -i
cd DracoPKG/lib ; qmake CONFIG+=libpkgsrc CONFIG+=staticlib PREFIX=$(pwd)/../build  && make install
cd ../../ ; qmake CONFIG+=libpkgsrc && make
```

```
./build/UserPKG
```

or

```
make install
```

or

```
make INSTALL_ROOT=$MYPKG install
```

